name: Troyer syndrome
descr: A hereditary spastic paraplegia that is characterized by spasticity of the leg muscles, progressive muscle weakness, paraplegia, muscle wasting in the hands and feet (distal amyotrophy), small stature, developmental delay, learning disorders, speech difficulties (dysarthria), and mood swings, and has_material_basis_in a mutation of the SPG20 gene.

name: Huntington's disease
descr: A neurodegenerative disease that has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance and is characterized by unwanted choreatic movements, behavioral and psychiatric disturbances and dementia and has_material_basis_in expansion of CAG triplet repeats (glutamine) resulting in neuron degeneration affecting muscle coordination, cognitive abilities.

name: cystic fibrosis
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by the buildup of thick, sticky mucus that can damage many organs.

name: glomerulosclerosis
descr: A glomerulonephritis that is characterized by hardening of the glomerulus in the kidney.
